File: Moody’s is the last of the three big international ratings agencies to have South African debt at investment grade. JOHANNESBURG - Ratings agency Moody’s says Government’s proposal to provide additional financial support to Eskom is “credit negative”. It says this will put further strain on fiscal resources. READ: NUM welcomes Eskom bailout, demands audit Finance Minister, Tito Mboweni, this week tabled an appropriation bill in Parliament to give Eskom an extra R59-billion of government support over two years. The ratings agency says without a clear turn-around strategy the utility is likely to require further bailouts. Moody’s is the last of the three big international ratings agencies to have South African debt at investment grade.